org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.tree.mxml

Class MXMLNodeBase.MXMLNodeInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.tree.mxml.MXMLNodeBase.MXMLNodeInfo
  • Enclosing class:
    MXMLNodeBase

    protected static class MXMLNodeBase.MXMLNodeInfo
extends Object
    MXML node classes can choose to create this object in createNodeInfo(). It then gets passed to the various methods involved in initializing one node, so that state can be conveyed between these methods, rather than having this state stored in fields of the node which would take up space after the node is completely initialized.

    It is currently used accumulate child nodes and source fragments.

      • hasDualContent

        public boolean hasDualContent
        A flag that keeps track of whether the tag had content that would conflict with the source attribute. For a Script, Style, or String tag, this is non-whitespace text content. For an XML or Model tag, this is a child tag.
